      </char>
    </note>ἀλλ᾽ ἐν τούτοις πᾶσιν ὑπερνικῶμεν διὰ τοῦ ἀγαπήσαντος ἡμᾶς. <verse number="38" style="v" />πέπεισμαι γὰρ ὅτι οὔτε θάνατος οὔτε ζωὴ οὔτε ἄγγελοι οὔτε ἀρχαὶ οὔτε ἐνεστῶτα οὔτε μέλλοντα οὔτε δυνάμεις<note caller="12" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">8.38 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε ἐνεστῶτα οὔτε μέλλοντα οὔτε δυνάμεις </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">27vid</char> (𝔓<char style="add">46</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">δύναμις</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) ℵ A B F G 365 1319 1506 1573 1739 1881 1962 2127 (it<char style="add">ar, d, f, g, o</char>) vg<char style="add">ww, st</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm eth slav Origen<char style="add">gr, lat2(2)/9</char> Eusebius Cyril; Jerome<char style="add">1(6)/7</char> Pelagius (Augustine<char style="add">5/8</char>) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε δυνάμεις οὔτε ἐνεστῶτα οὔτε μέλλοντα </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(Ψ <char style="it">l</char> 1365 <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε μέλλοντα </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">including</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε ὕψωμα</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 6 33 424 1175 1241 1912 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L] <char style="it">Lect</char><char style="add">pt, AD</char> it<char style="add">b, mon</char> geo<char style="add">2</char> Origen<char style="add">lat2/9</char> Chrysostom Theodore<char style="add">vid</char> Theodoret; (Ambrosiaster) Ambrose<char style="add">2/3</char> (Augustine<char style="add">1/8</char>) (it<char style="add">t</char> geo<char style="add">1</char> Origen<char style="add">lat1/9</char> Ambrose<char style="add">1/3</char> Augustine<char style="add">2/8</char> Quodvultdeus <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε δυνάμεις</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) LB DHH ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε ἐξουσίαι οὔτε ἐνεστῶτα οὔτε μέλλοντα οὔτε δυνάμεις </char><char style="ft" closed="false">C (D </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε ἐξουσίαι </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">before</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε ἀρχαί, </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D* </char><char style="fk" closed="false">δύναμις </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">instead of</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">δυνάμεις</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 81 104 256 263 459 (<char style="it">l</char> 590 <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε δυνάμεις</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (vg<char style="add">cl</char>) syr<char style="add">h with *</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> (Origen<char style="add">lat2/9</char>); (Hilary) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὔτε ἐξουσίαι οὔτε δυνάμεις οὔτε ἐνεστῶτα οὔτε μέλλοντα </char><char style="ft" closed="false">436 1852 <char style="it">Lect</char><char style="add">pt</char> syr<char style="add">p</char></char></note> <verse number="39" style="v" />οὔτε ὕψωμα οὔτε βάθος οὔτε τις κτίσις ἑτέρα δυνήσεται ἡμᾶς χωρίσαι ἀπὸ τῆς ἀγάπης τοῦ θεοῦ τῆς ἐν Χριστῷ Ἰησοῦ τῷ κυρίῳ ἡμῶν.</para>
  <chapter number="9" style="c" />
  <para style="s">God’s Election of Israel</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />Ἀλήθειαν λέγω ἐν Χριστῷ, οὐ ψεύδομαι, συμμαρτυρούσης μοι τῆς συνειδήσεώς μου ἐν πνεύματι ἁγίῳ, <verse number="2" style="v" />ὅτι λύπη μοί ἐστιν μεγάλη καὶ ἀδιάλειπτος ὀδύνη τῇ καρδίᾳ μου. <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.3 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 32:32">Ex 32.32</ref></char></note>ηὐχόμην γὰρ ἀνάθεμα εἶναι αὐτὸς ἐγὼ ἀπὸ τοῦ Χριστοῦ ὑπὲρ τῶν ἀδελφῶν μου τῶν συγγενῶν μου κατὰ σάρκα, <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἰσραηλῖται … υἱοθεσία </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 4:22">Ex 4.22</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 7:6">Dt 7.6</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 14:1-2">14.1‑2</ref></char></note>οἵτινές εἰσιν Ἰσραηλῖται, ὧν ἡ υἱοθεσία καὶ ἡ δόξα καὶ αἱ διαθῆκαι<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">9.4 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αἱ διαθῆκαι </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ C Ψ 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1881 1912 (1962 <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αἱ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 2127 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">d, f, g, mon, o</char> vg<char style="add">ww, st</char> syr<char style="add">p, h, (h<char style="add">gr</char>)</char> cop<char style="add">bo</char> arm geo slav Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Basil Diodore Epiphanius Chrysostom Proclus; Hilary<char style="add">1/2</char> Ambrosiaster Tyconius Jerome<char style="add">4/7</char> Pelagius Augustine<char style="add">5/6</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡ διαθήκη </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> B D F G 1852 <char style="it">l</char> 1154 it<char style="add">ar, b</char> vg<char style="add">cl</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> eth Theodore Cyril Hesychius; Cyprian Hilary<char style="add">1/2</char> Jerome<char style="add">3/7</char> Augustine<char style="add">1/6</char> BTI</char></note> καὶ ἡ νομοθεσία καὶ ἡ λατρεία καὶ αἱ ἐπαγγελίαι, <verse number="5" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.5 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐξ … σάρκα </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 1:1-16">Mt 1.1‑16</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:23-38">Lk 3.23‑38</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ ὢν ἐπὶ πάντων </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 1:1">Jn 1.1</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">θεὸς … ἀμήν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 41:13">Ps 41.13</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 1:25">Ro 1.25</ref></char></note>ὧν οἱ πατέρες καὶ ἐξ ὧν ὁ Χριστὸς τὸ κατὰ σάρκα,<note caller="a" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">9.5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">NO C: TOB ⫽ Period: GNB NRSV<char style="add">mg</char> REB EU<char style="add">mg</char> DHH<char style="add">mg</char> ⫽ Comma: NRSV REB<char style="add">mg</char> EU BJ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">||</char></note> ὁ ὢν ἐπὶ πάντων<note caller="b" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">9.5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Comma: WH (GNB) NRSV (REB) TOB ⫽ Period: NIV<char style="add">mg</char> REB<char style="add">mg</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">||</char></note> θεὸς<note caller="c" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">9.5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Comma: (GNB) NRSV<char style="add">mg</char> NIV REB EU LB ⫽ as text: M TR</char></note> εὐλογητὸς εἰς τοὺς αἰῶνας, ἀμήν.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">9.6 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Οὐχ … θεοῦ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="NUM 23:19">Nu 23.19</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οὐ … Ἰσραήλ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ROM 2:28">Ro 2.28</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Οὐχ οἷον δὲ ὅτι ἐκπέπτωκεν ὁ λόγος τοῦ θεοῦ. οὐ γὰρ πάντες οἱ ἐξ Ἰσραὴλ οὗτοι Ἰσραήλ· <verse number="7" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.7 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἐν … σπέρμα </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 21:12">Gn 21.12</ref></char></note>οὐδ᾽ ὅτι εἰσὶν σπέρμα Ἀβραὰμ πάντες τέκνα, ἀλλ᾽, <char style="qt">Ἐν Ἰσαὰκ κληθήσεταί σοι σπέρμα.</char> <verse number="8" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.8 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GAL 4:23">Ga 4.23</ref></char></note>τοῦτ᾽ ἔστιν, οὐ τὰ τέκνα τῆς σαρκὸς ταῦτα τέκνα τοῦ θεοῦ ἀλλὰ τὰ τέκνα τῆς ἐπαγγελίας λογίζεται εἰς σπέρμα. <verse number="9" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.9 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Κατὰ … υἱός </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 18:10">Gn 18.10</ref>, <ref loc="GEN 18:14">14</ref></char></note>ἐπαγγελίας γὰρ ὁ λόγος οὗτος, <char style="qt">Κατὰ τὸν καιρὸν τοῦτον ἐλεύσομαι καὶ ἔσται τῇ Σάρρᾳ υἱός.</char> <verse number="10" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.10 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 25:21">Gn 25.21</ref></char></note>οὐ μόνον δέ, ἀλλὰ καὶ Ῥεβέκκα ἐξ ἑνὸς κοίτην ἔχουσα, Ἰσαὰκ τοῦ πατρὸς ἡμῶν· <verse number="11" style="v" />μήπω γὰρ γεννηθέντων μηδὲ πραξάντων τι ἀγαθὸν ἢ φαῦλον, ἵνα ἡ κατ᾽ ἐκλογὴν πρόθεσις τοῦ θεοῦ μένῃ, <verse number="12" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.12 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ὁ μείζων … ἐλάσσονι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 25:23">Gn 25.23</ref></char></note>οὐκ ἐξ ἔργων ἀλλ᾽ ἐκ τοῦ καλοῦντος, ἐρρέθη αὐτῇ ὅτι <char style="qt">Ὁ μείζων δουλεύσει τῷ ἐλάσσονι,</char> <verse number="13" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.13 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Τὸν Ἰακὼβ … ἐμίσησα </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAL 1:2-3">Mal 1.2‑3</ref></char></note>καθὼς γέγραπται,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Τὸν Ἰακὼβ ἠγάπησα,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">τὸν δὲ Ἠσαῦ ἐμίσησα.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="14" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">9.14 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ ἀδικία … γένοιτο </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="DEU 32:4">Dt 32.4</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Τί οὖν ἐροῦμεν; μὴ ἀδικία παρὰ τῷ θεῷ; μὴ γένοιτο. <verse number="15" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.15 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἐλεήσω … οἰκτίρω </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 33:19">Ex 33.19</ref></char></note>τῷ Μωϋσεῖ γὰρ λέγει,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Ἐλεήσω ὃν ἂν ἐλεῶ</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ οἰκτιρήσω ὃν ἂν οἰκτίρω.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="16" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">9.16 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="EPH 2:8">Eph 2.8</ref>
      </char>
    </note>ἄρα οὖν οὐ τοῦ θέλοντος οὐδὲ τοῦ τρέχοντος ἀλλὰ τοῦ ἐλεῶντος θεοῦ. <verse number="17" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.17 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Εἰς … γῇ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 9:16">Ex 9.16</ref></char></note>λέγει γὰρ ἡ γραφὴ τῷ Φαραὼ ὅτι <char style="qt">Εἰς αὐτὸ τοῦτο ἐξήγειρά σε ὅπως ἐνδείξωμαι ἐν σοὶ τὴν δύναμίν μου καὶ ὅπως διαγγελῇ τὸ ὄνομά μου ἐν πάσῃ τῇ γῇ.</char> <verse number="18" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.18 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὃν δὲ θέλει σκληρύνει </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 4:21">Ex 4.21</ref>; <ref loc="EXO 7:3">7.3</ref>; <ref loc="EXO 9:12">9.12</ref>; <ref loc="EXO 14:4">14.4</ref>, <ref loc="EXO 14:17">17</ref></char></note>ἄρα οὖν ὃν θέλει ἐλεεῖ, ὃν δὲ θέλει σκληρύνει.</para>
  <para style="s">God’s Wrath and Mercy</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" />Ἐρεῖς μοι οὖν, Τί [οὖν] ἔτι μέμφεται; τῷ γὰρ βουλήματι αὐτοῦ τίς ἀνθέστηκεν; <verse number="20" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.20 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ ἐρεῖ … πλάσαντι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 29:16">Is 29.16</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 45:9">45.9</ref>; <ref loc="WIS 12:12">Wsd 12.12</ref></char></note>ὦ ἄνθρωπε, μενοῦνγε σὺ τίς εἶ ὁ ἀνταποκρινόμενος τῷ θεῷ; μὴ ἐρεῖ τὸ πλάσμα τῷ πλάσαντι, Τί με ἐποίησας οὕτως; <verse number="21" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.21 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οὐκ … πηλοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JER 18:6">Jr 18.6</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐκ τοῦ … ἀτιμίαν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="WIS 15:7">Wsd 15.7</ref></char></note>ἢ οὐκ ἔχει ἐξουσίαν ὁ κεραμεὺς τοῦ πηλοῦ ἐκ τοῦ αὐτοῦ φυράματος ποιῆσαι ὃ μὲν εἰς τιμὴν σκεῦος ὃ δὲ εἰς ἀτιμίαν; <verse number="22" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.22 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἤνεγκεν … ὀργῆς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JER 50:25">Jr 50.25</ref></char></note>εἰ δὲ θέλων ὁ θεὸς ἐνδείξασθαι τὴν ὀργὴν καὶ γνωρίσαι τὸ δυνατὸν αὐτοῦ ἤνεγκεν ἐν πολλῇ μακροθυμίᾳ σκεύη ὀργῆς κατηρτισμένα εἰς ἀπώλειαν, <verse number="23" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EPH 1:3-12">Eph 1.3‑12</ref></char></note>καὶ ἵνα<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">9.23 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ ἵνα </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46vid</char> ℵ A D F G Ψ 33 81 104 256 263 365 424* 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1852 1881 1962 2127 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">d, f, g, mon, o</char> vg<char style="add">ms</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">pt</char></char> eth geo slav Chrysostom; Ambrosiaster Pelagius Augustine Julian-Eclanum ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἵνα </char><char style="ft" closed="false">B 6 424<char style="add">c</char> 436 1912 it<char style="add">ar, b</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo<char style="add">pt</char></char> arm Origen<char style="add">gr, lat</char> Severian; Jerome LB? BJ</char></note> γνωρίσῃ τὸν πλοῦτον τῆς δόξης αὐτοῦ ἐπὶ σκεύη ἐλέους ἃ προητοίμασεν εἰς δόξαν; <verse number="24" style="v" />οὓς καὶ ἐκάλεσεν ἡμᾶς οὐ μόνον ἐξ Ἰουδαίων ἀλλὰ καὶ ἐξ ἐθνῶν, <verse number="25" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.25 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Καλέσω … ἠγαπημένην </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="HOS 2:23">Ho 2.23</ref></char></note>ὡς καὶ ἐν τῷ Ὡσηὲ λέγει,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Καλέσω τὸν οὐ λαόν μου λαόν μου</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ τὴν οὐκ ἠγαπημένην ἠγαπημένην·</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="26" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">9.26 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="HOS 1:10">Ho 1.10</ref>
      </char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">καὶ ἔσται ἐν τῷ τόπῳ οὗ ἐρρέθη αὐτοῖς, Οὐ λαός μου ὑμεῖς,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἐκεῖ κληθήσονται υἱοὶ θεοῦ ζῶντος.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="27" style="v" />Ἠσαΐας δὲ κράζει ὑπὲρ τοῦ Ἰσραήλ, <char style="qt">Ἐὰν ᾖ ὁ ἀριθμὸς τῶν υἱῶν Ἰσραὴλ ὡς ἡ ἄμμος τῆς θαλάσσης, τὸ ὑπόλειμμα σωθήσεται·</char> <verse number="28" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.27‑28 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἐὰν … γῆς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 10:22-23">Is 10.22‑23</ref>; <ref loc="HOS 1:10">Ho 1.10</ref></char></note><char style="qt">λόγον γὰρ συντελῶν καὶ συντέμνων</char><note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">9.28 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">συντέμνων </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> ℵ* A B 6 424<char style="add">c</char> 1319 1506 1739 1881 it<char style="add">mon*</char> syr<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> eth Eusebius<char style="add">2/3</char> Cyril (Theodoret<char style="add">lem</char>); Ps-Cyprian Ambrose Gaudentius Jerome<char style="add">1/4</char> Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">συντέμνων ἐν δικαιοσύνῃ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">81 436 1852 Jerome<char style="add">1/4</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">συντέμνων ἐν δικαιοσύνῃ ὅτι λόγον συντετμημένον </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(<char style="it">see</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ISA 10:22-23">Is 10.22‑23</ref>)</char> ℵ<char style="add">2</char> D F G Ψ 33 104 256 263 365 424* 459 1175 1241 1573 1912 1962 2127 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 809 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">συντετριμμένον</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, g, mon<char style="add">2</char>, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> arm geo slav Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Chrysostom (Eusebius<char style="add">1/3</char>); Ambrosiaster Jerome<char style="add">2/4</char> Pelagius</char></note> <char style="qt">ποιήσει κύριος ἐπὶ τῆς γῆς.</char> <verse number="29" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.29 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Εἰ … ὡμοιώθημεν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 1:9">Is 1.9</ref></char></note>καὶ καθὼς προείρηκεν Ἠσαΐας,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Εἰ μὴ κύριος Σαβαὼθ ἐγκατέλιπεν ἡμῖν σπέρμα,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ὡς Σόδομα ἂν ἐγενήθημεν</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ ὡς Γόμορρα ἂν ὡμοιώθημεν.</char></para>
  <para style="s">Israel and the Gospel</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="30" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">9.30 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ROM 10:20">Ro 10.20</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Τί οὖν ἐροῦμεν; ὅτι ἔθνη τὰ μὴ διώκοντα δικαιοσύνην κατέλαβεν δικαιοσύνην, δικαιοσύνην δὲ τὴν ἐκ πίστεως, <verse number="31" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.31 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="WIS 2:11">Wsd 2.11</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 10:2-3">Ro 10.2‑3</ref></char></note>Ἰσραὴλ δὲ διώκων νόμον δικαιοσύνης εἰς νόμον οὐκ ἔφθασεν. <verse number="32" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.32 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῷ λίθῳ τοῦ προσκόμματος </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 8:14">Is 8.14</ref></char></note>διὰ τί; ὅτι οὐκ ἐκ πίστεως ἀλλ᾽ ὡς ἐξ ἔργων<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">9.32 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἔργων </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46vid</char> ℵ* A B F G 6 424<char style="add">c</char> 1739 1881 2200 it<char style="add">ar, b, f, g, mon, o</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> Origen<char style="add">lat</char>; Ambrosiaster Jerome Pelagius Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἔργων νόμου </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> D Ψ 33 81 104 256 263 365 424* 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1852 1912 1962 2127 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">d</char> vg<char style="add">ms</char> syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> arm eth geo slav Diodore<char style="add">vid</char> Chrysostom</char></note>· προσέκοψαν τῷ λίθῳ τοῦ προσκόμματος, <verse number="33" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">9.33 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἰδοὺ … καταισχυνθήσεται </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 28:16">Is 28.16</ref> (<ref loc="ROM 10:11">Ro 10.11</ref>; <ref loc="1PE 2:6">1 Pe 2.6</ref>, <ref loc="1PE 2:8">8</ref>)</char></note>καθὼς γέγραπται,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Ἰδοὺ τίθημι ἐν Σιὼν λίθον προσκόμματος καὶ πέτραν σκανδάλου,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ</char>
    <note caller="5" style="f">
      <char style="fr" closed="false">9.33 </char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char>
      <char style="fk" closed="false">καί </char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B D F G 81 1506 1881 it<char style="add">b, d*, f, g, mon</char> syr<char style="add">p, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm<char style="add">ms</char> eth Origen<char style="add">gr, lat</char> Cyril; Ambrosiaster Augustine ⫽ </char>
      <char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ πᾶς </char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">(<char style="it">see</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 10:11">10.11</ref>)</char> Ψ 6 33 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1573 1739 1852 1912 1962 2127 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, d<char style="add">2</char>, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> arm<char style="add">ms</char> geo slav Didymus<char style="add">dub</char> Chrysostom Theodore; Pelagius</char>
    </note> <char style="qt">ὁ πιστεύων ἐπ᾽ αὐτῷ οὐ καταισχυνθήσεται.</char></para>
  <chapter number="10" style="c" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />Ἀδελφοί, ἡ μὲν εὐδοκία τῆς ἐμῆς καρδίας καὶ ἡ δέησις πρὸς τὸν θεὸν ὑπὲρ αὐτῶν<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">10.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> ℵ* A B D F G 6 256 365 1319* 1506 1573 1739 1881 1912 1962 2127 it<char style="add">d*, f, g, mon</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> Cyril; Ambrosiaster Augustine<char style="add">5/9</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτῶν ἐστιν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> P Ψ 33 263 1852 <char style="it">l</char> 60 it<char style="add">ar, b, d<char style="add">2</char>, o</char> vg arm geo<char style="add">1</char> Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Chrysostom; Pelagius Augustine<char style="add">4/9</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τοῦ Ἰσραήλ ἐστιν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">81 104 424 436 459 1175 1241 (1319<char style="add">c</char> <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐστιν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L] <char style="it">Lect</char> (eth) geo<char style="add">2</char> slav (Marcion<char style="add">acc. to Tertullian</char>) BTI DHH?</char></note> εἰς σωτηρίαν. <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.2 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ζῆλον θεοῦ ἔχουσιν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 22:3">Ac 22.3</ref></char></note>μαρτυρῶ γὰρ αὐτοῖς ὅτι ζῆλον θεοῦ ἔχουσιν ἀλλ᾽ οὐ κατ᾽ ἐπίγνωσιν· <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.3 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 9:31-32">Ro 9.31‑32</ref></char></note>ἀγνοοῦντες γὰρ τὴν τοῦ θεοῦ δικαιοσύνην καὶ τὴν ἰδίαν [δικαιοσύνην] ζητοῦντες στῆσαι, τῇ δικαιοσύνῃ τοῦ θεοῦ οὐχ ὑπετάγησαν· <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 5:17">Mt 5.17</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 3:18">Jn 3.18</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 8:13">He 8.13</ref></char></note>τέλος γὰρ νόμου Χριστὸς εἰς δικαιοσύνην παντὶ τῷ πιστεύοντι.</para>
  <para style="s">Salvation for All</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">10.5 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LEV 18:5">Lv 18.5</ref>; <ref loc="GAL 3:12">Ga 3.12</ref></char>
    </note>Μωϋσῆς γὰρ γράφει τὴν δικαιοσύνην τὴν ἐκ [τοῦ] νόμου ὅτι <char style="qt">ὁ ποιήσας</char> αὐτὰ <char style="qt">ἄνθρωπος ζήσεται ἐν αὐτοῖς.</char> <verse number="6" style="v" />ἡ δὲ ἐκ πίστεως δικαιοσύνη οὕτως λέγει, <char style="qt">Μὴ εἴπῃς ἐν τῇ καρδίᾳ σου, Τίς ἀναβήσεται εἰς τὸν οὐρανόν;</char> τοῦτ᾽ ἔστιν Χριστὸν καταγαγεῖν· <verse number="7" style="v" />ἤ, <char style="qt">Τίς καταβήσεται εἰς τὴν ἄβυσσον;</char> τοῦτ᾽ ἔστιν Χριστὸν ἐκ νεκρῶν ἀναγαγεῖν. <verse number="8" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.6‑8 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Μὴ εἴπῃς … καρδίᾳ σου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 9:4">Dt 9.4</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 30:12-14">30.12‑14</ref></char></note>ἀλλὰ τί λέγει;</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Ἐγγύς σου τὸ ῥῆμά ἐστιν</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἐν τῷ στόματί σου καὶ ἐν τῇ καρδίᾳ σου,</char></para>
  <para style="m">τοῦτ᾽ ἔστιν τὸ ῥῆμα τῆς πίστεως ὃ κηρύσσομεν. <verse number="9" style="v" />ὅτι ἐὰν ὁμολογήσῃς ἐν τῷ στόματί σου κύριον Ἰησοῦν καὶ πιστεύσῃς ἐν τῇ καρδίᾳ σου ὅτι ὁ θεὸς αὐτὸν ἤγειρεν ἐκ νεκρῶν, σωθήσῃ· <verse number="10" style="v" />καρδίᾳ γὰρ πιστεύεται εἰς δικαιοσύνην, στόματι δὲ ὁμολογεῖται εἰς σωτηρίαν. <verse number="11" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.11 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ πιστεύων … καταισχυνθήσεται </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 28:16">Is 28.16</ref> (<ref loc="ROM 9:33">Ro 9.33</ref>)</char></note>λέγει γὰρ ἡ γραφή, Πᾶς <char style="qt">ὁ πιστεύων ἐπ᾽ αὐτῷ οὐ καταισχυνθήσεται.</char> <verse number="12" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.12 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οὐ … Ἕλληνος </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 10:34">Ac 10.34</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 15:9">15.9</ref></char></note>οὐ γάρ ἐστιν διαστολὴ Ἰουδαίου τε καὶ Ἕλληνος, ὁ γὰρ αὐτὸς κύριος πάντων, πλουτῶν εἰς πάντας τοὺς ἐπικαλουμένους αὐτόν· <verse number="13" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.13 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Πᾶς … σωθήσεται </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JOL 2:32">Jl 2.32</ref></char></note><char style="qt">Πᾶς</char> γὰρ <char style="qt">ὃς ἂν ἐπικαλέσηται τὸ ὄνομα κυρίου σωθήσεται.</char></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" />Πῶς οὖν ἐπικαλέσωνται εἰς ὃν οὐκ ἐπίστευσαν; πῶς δὲ πιστεύσωσιν οὗ οὐκ ἤκουσαν; πῶς δὲ ἀκούσωσιν χωρὶς κηρύσσοντος; <verse number="15" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.15 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ὡς … ἀγαθά </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 52:7">Is 52.7</ref>; <ref loc="NAM 1:15">Na 1.15</ref>; <ref loc="EPH 6:15">Eph 6.15</ref></char></note>πῶς δὲ κηρύξωσιν ἐὰν μὴ ἀποσταλῶσιν; καθὼς γέγραπται, <char style="qt">Ὡς ὡραῖοι οἱ πόδες</char><note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">10.15 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πόδες </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> ℵ* A B C 81 1506 1739 1881 1912 2200 <char style="it">l</char> 422 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 it<char style="add">ar</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> eth slav<char style="add">ms</char> Clement Ps-Hippolytus Origen<char style="add">gr, lat</char> Philo-Carpasia Severian Cyril<char style="add">1/2</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πόδες τῶν εὐαγγελιζομένων εἰρήνην </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> D F G Ψ 6 33 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1573 1852 1962 2127 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">b, d, f, g, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> arm geo slav<char style="add">ms</char> Marcion<char style="add">acc. to Tertullian</char> (Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char>) Adamantius (Eusebius) Apollinaris Chrysostom Cyril<char style="add">1/2</char> Hesychius; Hilary Ambrosiaster Ambrose Jerome Pelagius Augustine</char></note> <char style="qt">τῶν εὐαγγελιζομένων [τὰ] ἀγαθά.</char> <verse number="16" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.16 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Κύριε … ἡμῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 53:1">Is 53.1</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 12:38">Jn 12.38</ref></char></note>Ἀλλ᾽ οὐ πάντες ὑπήκουσαν τῷ εὐαγγελίῳ. Ἠσαΐας γὰρ λέγει, <char style="qt">Κύριε, τίς ἐπίστευσεν τῇ ἀκοῇ ἡμῶν;</char> <verse number="17" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.17 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἡ πίστις ἐξ ἀκοῆς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 17:20">Jn 17.20</ref></char></note>ἄρα ἡ πίστις ἐξ ἀκοῆς, ἡ δὲ ἀκοὴ διὰ ῥήματος Χριστοῦ<note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">10.17 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Χριστοῦ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46vid</char> ℵ* B C<char style="add">vid</char> D* 6 81 1506 1739 1852 it<char style="add">ar, b, d</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm Origen<char style="add">lat</char>; Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">θεοῦ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">1</char> A D<char style="add">1</char> Ψ 33 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1573 1881 1912 1962 2127 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> eth<char style="add">pp</char> geo slav Clement Basil Chrysostom Theodore; Gaudentius Jerome Sedulius-Scotus ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> F G it<char style="add">f, g, o</char> Hilary Ambrosiaster Pelagius</char></note>. <verse number="18" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">10.18 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Εἰς πᾶσαν … αὐτῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 19:4">Ps 19.4</ref></char></note>ἀλλὰ λέγω, μὴ οὐκ ἤκουσαν; μενοῦνγε·</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Εἰς πᾶσαν τὴν γῆν ἐξῆλθεν ὁ φθόγγος αὐτῶν</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ εἰς τὰ πέρατα τῆς οἰκουμένης τὰ ῥήματα αὐτῶν.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="19" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">10.19 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Ἐγὼ … παροργιῶ ὑμᾶς </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="DEU 32:21">Dt 32.21</ref>
      </char>
    </note>ἀλλὰ λέγω, μὴ Ἰσραὴλ οὐκ ἔγνω; πρῶτος Μωϋσῆς λέγει,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Ἐγὼ παραζηλώσω</char> ὑμᾶς <char style="qt">ἐπ᾽ οὐκ ἔθνει,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἐπ᾽ ἔθνει ἀσυνέτῳ παροργιῶ</char> ὑμᾶς.</para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="20" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">10.20 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Εὑρέθην … ἐπερωτῶσιν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ISA 65:1">Is 65.1</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Ἠσαΐας δὲ ἀποτολμᾷ καὶ λέγει,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Εὑρέθην</char> [ἐν] <char style="qt">τοῖς ἐμὲ μὴ ζητοῦσιν,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἐμφανὴς ἐγενόμην τοῖς ἐμὲ μὴ ἐπερωτῶσιν.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="21" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">10.21 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Ὅλην … ἀντιλέγοντα </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ISA 65:2">Is 65.2</ref> <char style="sc">lxx</char></char>
    </note>πρὸς δὲ τὸν Ἰσραὴλ λέγει, <char style="qt">Ὅλην τὴν ἡμέραν ἐξεπέτασα τὰς χεῖράς μου πρὸς λαὸν ἀπειθοῦντα καὶ ἀντιλέγοντα.</char></para>
  <chapter number="11" style="c" />
  <para style="s">The Remnant of Israel</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.1 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἐγὼ … Βενιαμίν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="PHP 3:5">Php 3.5</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Λέγω οὖν, μὴ ἀπώσατο ὁ θεὸς τὸν λαὸν<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὸν λαόν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C D Ψ 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1852 1881 1912 1962 2127 2200 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, d</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm eth geo slav Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Eusebius Chrysostom Cyril; Jerome Pelagius Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὴν κληρονομίαν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> F G it<char style="add">b, f, g, o</char> Ambrosiaster Tyconius Ambrose Sedulius-Scotus</char></note> αὐτοῦ; μὴ γένοιτο· καὶ γὰρ ἐγὼ Ἰσραηλίτης εἰμί, ἐκ σπέρματος Ἀβραάμ, φυλῆς Βενιαμίν. <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.1‑2 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ γένοιτο … λαὸν αὐτοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1SA 12:22">1 Sm 12.22</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 94:14">Ps 94.14</ref></char></note>οὐκ ἀπώσατο ὁ θεὸς τὸν λαὸν αὐτοῦ ὃν προέγνω. ἢ οὐκ οἴδατε ἐν Ἠλίᾳ τί λέγει ἡ γραφή, ὡς ἐντυγχάνει τῷ θεῷ κατὰ τοῦ Ἰσραήλ; <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.3 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Κύριε … μου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1KI 19:10">1 Kgs 19.10</ref>, <ref loc="1KI 19:14">14</ref></char></note>Κύριε, <char style="qt">τοὺς προφήτας σου ἀπέκτειναν, τὰ θυσιαστήριά σου κατέσκαψαν, κἀγὼ ὑπελείφθην μόνος καὶ ζητοῦσιν τὴν ψυχήν μου.</char> <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Κατέλιπον … Βάαλ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1KI 19:18">1 Kgs 19.18</ref></char></note>ἀλλὰ τί λέγει αὐτῷ ὁ χρηματισμός; <char style="qt">Κατέλιπον</char> ἐμαυτῷ <char style="qt">ἑπτακισχιλίους ἄνδρας, οἵτινες οὐκ ἔκαμψαν γόνυ τῇ Βάαλ.</char> <verse number="5" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.5 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 9:27">Ro 9.27</ref></char></note>οὕτως οὖν καὶ ἐν τῷ νῦν καιρῷ λεῖμμα κατ᾽ ἐκλογὴν χάριτος γέγονεν· <verse number="6" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.6 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GAL 3:18">Ga 3.18</ref></char></note>εἰ δὲ χάριτι, οὐκέτι ἐξ ἔργων, ἐπεὶ ἡ χάρις οὐκέτι γίνεται χάρις<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.6 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">χάρις </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> ℵ* A C D F G P (81 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">χάρις γίνεται</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 263 1506<char style="add">vid</char> 1739 1852 1881 2200 it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, g, o</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm (eth) geo<char style="add">1</char> Origen<char style="add">gr, lat</char> Didymus<char style="add">vid</char> Cyril; Ambrosiaster Ambrose Jerome Pelagius Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">χάρις, ἐπεὶ τὸ ἔργον οὐκέτι ἐστὶν ἔργον </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">l</char> 603 slav<char style="add">ms</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">χάρις. εἰ δὲ ἐξ ἔργων, οὐκέτι ἐστὶν χάρις, ἐπεὶ τὸ ἔργον οὐκέτι ἐστὶν ἔργον </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> (B <char style="it">omit first</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐστίν </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">and read</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">χάρις </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">for final</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἔργον</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) Ψ 6 33<char style="add">vid</char> 104 256 (365) 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1573 1912 (1962 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡ χάρις </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">for</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐστὶν χάρις </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">and</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐκ ἔστιν ἔργον</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 2127 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 1178 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐκ ἔστιν ἔργον</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) vg<char style="add">ms</char> (syr<char style="add">p, h</char>) geo<char style="add">2</char> slav<char style="add">ms</char> Chrysostom</char></note>. <verse number="7" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.7 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὃ … ἐπέτυχεν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 9:31">Ro 9.31</ref></char></note>τί οὖν; ὃ ἐπιζητεῖ Ἰσραήλ, τοῦτο οὐκ ἐπέτυχεν, ἡ δὲ ἐκλογὴ ἐπέτυχεν· οἱ δὲ λοιποὶ ἐπωρώθησαν, <verse number="8" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.8 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἔδωκεν … ἡμέρας </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 29:4">Dt 29.4</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 29:10">Is 29.10</ref></char></note>καθὼς γέγραπται,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Ἔδωκεν αὐτοῖς ὁ θεὸς πνεῦμα κατανύξεως,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ὀφθαλμοὺς τοῦ μὴ βλέπειν</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ ὦτα τοῦ μὴ ἀκούειν,</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">ἕως τῆς σήμερον ἡμέρας.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="9" style="v" />καὶ Δαυὶδ λέγει,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Γενηθήτω ἡ τράπεζα αὐτῶν εἰς παγίδα</char> καὶ εἰς θήραν</para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ εἰς σκάνδαλον καὶ εἰς ἀνταπόδομα αὐτοῖς,</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="10" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.9‑10 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Γενηθήτω … σύγκαμψον </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="PSA 69:22-23">Ps 69.22‑23</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 35:8">35.8</ref></char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">σκοτισθήτωσαν οἱ ὀφθαλμοὶ αὐτῶν τοῦ μὴ βλέπειν</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ τὸν νῶτον αὐτῶν διὰ παντὸς σύγκαμψον.</char></para>
  <para style="s">The Salvation of the Gentiles</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.11 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">τῷ αὐτῶν … ἔθνεσιν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 13:46">Ac 13.46</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">εἰς … αὐτούς </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="DEU 32:21">Dt 32.21</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 10:19">Ro 10.19</ref></char>
    </note>Λέγω οὖν, μὴ ἔπταισαν ἵνα πέσωσιν; μὴ γένοιτο· ἀλλὰ τῷ αὐτῶν παραπτώματι ἡ σωτηρία τοῖς ἔθνεσιν εἰς τὸ παραζηλῶσαι αὐτούς. <verse number="12" style="v" />εἰ δὲ τὸ παράπτωμα αὐτῶν πλοῦτος κόσμου καὶ τὸ ἥττημα αὐτῶν πλοῦτος ἐθνῶν, πόσῳ μᾶλλον τὸ πλήρωμα αὐτῶν.<note caller="a" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.12 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Question: AD TR TOB</char></note></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" />Ὑμῖν δὲ λέγω τοῖς ἔθνεσιν· ἐφ᾽ ὅσον μὲν οὖν εἰμι ἐγὼ ἐθνῶν ἀπόστολος, τὴν διακονίαν μου δοξάζω, <verse number="14" style="v" />εἴ πως παραζηλώσω μου τὴν σάρκα καὶ σώσω τινὰς ἐξ αὐτῶν. <verse number="15" style="v" />εἰ γὰρ ἡ ἀποβολὴ αὐτῶν καταλλαγὴ κόσμου, τίς ἡ πρόσλημψις εἰ μὴ ζωὴ ἐκ νεκρῶν; <verse number="16" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.16 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">εἰ δὲ … φύραμα </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="NUM 15:17-21">Nu 15.17‑21</ref>; <ref loc="NEH 10:37">Ne 10.37</ref>; <ref loc="EZK 44:30">Eze 44.30</ref></char></note>εἰ δὲ ἡ ἀπαρχὴ ἁγία, καὶ τὸ φύραμα· καὶ εἰ ἡ ῥίζα ἁγία, καὶ οἱ κλάδοι.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.17 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="EPH 2:11-19">Eph 2.11‑19</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Εἰ δέ τινες τῶν κλάδων ἐξεκλάσθησαν, σὺ δὲ ἀγριέλαιος ὢν ἐνεκεντρίσθης ἐν αὐτοῖς καὶ συγκοινωνὸς τῆς ῥίζης τῆς πιότητος<note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.17 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ῥίζης τῆς πιότητος </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ* B C Ψ 1175 1506 1912 2464 <char style="it">l</char> 599 it<char style="add">b, o</char> (cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char>) Origen<char style="add">lat1/4</char>; Gildas ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ῥίζης καὶ τῆς πιότητος </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> A D<char style="add">2</char> 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1241 1319 1573 1739 1852 1881 1962 2127 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> arm geo slav Origen<char style="add">lat3/4</char> Chrysostom Cyril; Pelagius Augustine<char style="add">2/5</char> LB BTI ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς πιότητος </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> D* F G it<char style="add">d, f, g</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">ms</char>, fay</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char>; Pacian Augustine<char style="add">3/5</char> BJ ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ῥίζης </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(eth) Ambrosiaster</char></note> τῆς ἐλαίας ἐγένου, <verse number="18" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.18 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οὐ … ῥίζα σέ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 4:22">Jn 4.22</ref></char></note>μὴ κατακαυχῶ τῶν κλάδων· εἰ δὲ κατακαυχᾶσαι οὐ σὺ τὴν ῥίζαν βαστάζεις ἀλλ᾽ ἡ ῥίζα σέ. <verse number="19" style="v" />ἐρεῖς οὖν, Ἐξεκλάσθησαν κλάδοι ἵνα ἐγὼ ἐγκεντρισθῶ. <verse number="20" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.20 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ ὑψηλὰ φρόνει </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 12:16">Ro 12.16</ref></char></note>καλῶς· τῇ ἀπιστίᾳ ἐξεκλάσθησαν, σὺ δὲ τῇ πίστει ἕστηκας. μὴ ὑψηλὰ φρόνει ἀλλὰ φοβοῦ· <verse number="21" style="v" />εἰ γὰρ ὁ θεὸς τῶν κατὰ φύσιν κλάδων οὐκ ἐφείσατο, [μή πως] οὐδὲ<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.21 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">μή πως οὐδέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> D F G Ψ 33 104 424* 459 1175 1241 1912 1962 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 592 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">μηδέ; </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">l</char> 422 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">δέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">for</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐδέ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, g, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> arm (eth) (geo) slav Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Chrysostom Severian; Cyprian Ambrosiaster Pelagius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐδέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C P 6 81 256 263 365 424<char style="add">c</char> 436 1319 1506 1573 1739 1852 1881 2127 2200 <char style="it">l</char> 593 <char style="it">l</char> 599 cop<char style="add">sa, bo, fay</char> Origen<char style="add">lat</char>; Gregory-Elvira Augustine NIV REB EU TOB BTI DHH?</char></note> σοῦ φείσεται. <verse number="22" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.22 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 15:2">Jn 15.2</ref>, <ref loc="JHN 15:4">4</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐὰν … χρηστότητι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="HEB 3:14">He 3.14</ref></char></note>ἴδε οὖν χρηστότητα καὶ ἀποτομίαν θεοῦ· ἐπὶ μὲν τοὺς πεσόντας ἀποτομία, ἐπὶ δὲ σὲ χρηστότης θεοῦ, ἐὰν ἐπιμένῃς τῇ χρηστότητι, ἐπεὶ καὶ σὺ ἐκκοπήσῃ. <verse number="23" style="v" />κἀκεῖνοι δέ, ἐὰν μὴ ἐπιμένωσιν τῇ ἀπιστίᾳ, ἐγκεντρισθήσονται· δυνατὸς γάρ ἐστιν ὁ θεὸς πάλιν ἐγκεντρίσαι αὐτούς. <verse number="24" style="v" />εἰ γὰρ σὺ ἐκ τῆς κατὰ φύσιν ἐξεκόπης ἀγριελαίου καὶ παρὰ φύσιν ἐνεκεντρίσθης εἰς καλλιέλαιον, πόσῳ μᾶλλον οὗτοι οἱ κατὰ φύσιν ἐγκεντρισθήσονται τῇ ἰδίᾳ ἐλαίᾳ.<note caller="b" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.24 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Question: AD TR</char></note></para>
  <para style="s">The Restoration of Israel</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="25" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.25 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ … φρόνιμοι </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ROM 12:16">Ro 12.16</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">τὸ πλήρωμα … εἰσέλθῃ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 21:24">Lk 21.24</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 10:16">Jn 10.16</ref></char>
    </note>Οὐ γὰρ θέλω ὑμᾶς ἀγνοεῖν, ἀδελφοί, τὸ μυστήριον τοῦτο, ἵνα μὴ ἦτε [παρ᾽]<note caller="5" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.25 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">παρ᾽ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ C D 33 81 104 256 263 365 424* 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1573 1881 1912 1962 2127 2464 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 883 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καθ᾽</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">b</char> slav Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Chrysostom Theodore Hesychius<char style="add">lat</char>; Gregory-Elvira Jerome<char style="add">1/3</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">A B 1506 1852 2200 syr<char style="add">p, h</char> arm ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> 𝔓<char style="add">46</char> F G Ψ 6 424<char style="add">c</char> 1739 it<char style="add">ar, d, f, g, o</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo, fay</char> Hilary Ambrosiaster Jerome<char style="add">2/3</char> Pelagius Augustine</char></note> ἑαυτοῖς φρόνιμοι, ὅτι πώρωσις ἀπὸ μέρους τῷ Ἰσραὴλ γέγονεν ἄχρι οὗ τὸ πλήρωμα τῶν ἐθνῶν εἰσέλθῃ <verse number="26" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.26 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">πᾶς Ἰσραὴλ σωθήσεται </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 23:39">Mt 23.39</ref></char></note>καὶ οὕτως πᾶς Ἰσραὴλ σωθήσεται, καθὼς γέγραπται,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Ἥξει ἐκ Σιὼν ὁ ῥυόμενος,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἀποστρέψει ἀσεβείας ἀπὸ Ἰακώβ.</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="27" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.26‑27 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Ἥξει … διαθήκη </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ISA 59:20-21">Is 59.20‑21</ref> (<ref loc="PSA 14:7">Ps 14.7</ref>)</char>
    </note>
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.27 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ὅταν … αὐτῶν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ISA 27:9">Is 27.9</ref>; <ref loc="JER 31:33-34">Jr 31.33‑34</ref></char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">καὶ αὕτη αὐτοῖς ἡ παρ᾽ ἐμοῦ διαθήκη,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ὅταν ἀφέλωμαι τὰς ἁμαρτίας αὐτῶν.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="28" style="v" />κατὰ μὲν τὸ εὐαγγέλιον ἐχθροὶ δι᾽ ὑμᾶς, κατὰ δὲ τὴν ἐκλογὴν ἀγαπητοὶ διὰ τοὺς πατέρας· <verse number="29" style="v" />ἀμεταμέλητα γὰρ τὰ χαρίσματα καὶ ἡ κλῆσις τοῦ θεοῦ. <verse number="30" style="v" />ὥσπερ γὰρ ὑμεῖς ποτε ἠπειθήσατε τῷ θεῷ, νῦν δὲ ἠλεήθητε τῇ τούτων ἀπειθείᾳ, <verse number="31" style="v" />οὕτως καὶ οὗτοι νῦν ἠπείθησαν τῷ ὑμετέρῳ ἐλέει, ἵνα καὶ αὐτοὶ [νῦν]<note caller="6" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.31 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">νῦν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ B D<char style="add">*, 3</char> 1506 cop<char style="add">bo, fay<char style="add">ms</char></char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὕστερον </char><char style="ft" closed="false">33 256 263 365 1319 1573 1852 1912 1962 2127 cop<char style="add">sa, fay<char style="add">ms</char></char> slav Ambrosiaster<char style="add">mss</char> BTI ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> 𝔓<char style="add">46</char> A D<char style="add">2</char> F G Ψ 6 81 104 424 436 459 1175 1241 1739 1881 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, g, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">p</char> arm eth geo Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Diodore Didymus Chrysostom; Ambrosiaster Ambrose Jerome Pelagius Augustine REB</char></note> ἐλεηθῶσιν. <verse number="32" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">11.32 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GAL 3:22">Ga 3.22</ref>; <ref loc="1TI 2:4">1 Tm 2.4</ref></char></note>συνέκλεισεν γὰρ ὁ θεὸς τοὺς πάντας<note caller="7" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.32 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τοὺς πάντας </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B D<char style="add">2</char> Ψ 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1852 1881 1912 1962 2127 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, fay</char> arm eth geo Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Diodore Didymus Chrysostom Theodore<char style="add">lat</char> Cyril<char style="add">1/3</char> (John-Damascus); Ambrosiaster<char style="add">mss</char> Jerome<char style="add">5/17</char> Augustine<char style="add">9/10</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὰ πάντα </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46vid</char> D* (F G <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τά</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, g, o</char> vg Irenaeus<char style="add">(gr), lat</char> Cyril<char style="add">2/3</char>; Ambrosiaster Priscillian Ambrose Jerome<char style="add">12/17</char> Augustine<char style="add">1/10</char></char></note> εἰς ἀπείθειαν, ἵνα τοὺς πάντας ἐλεήσῃ.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="33" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.33 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἀνεξιχνίαστοι … αὐτοῦ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ISA 45:15">Is 45.15</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 55:8">55.8</ref></char>
    </note>Ὦ βάθος πλούτου καὶ σοφίας καὶ γνώσεως θεοῦ· ὡς ἀνεξεραύνητα τὰ κρίματα αὐτοῦ καὶ ἀνεξιχνίαστοι αἱ ὁδοὶ αὐτοῦ.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="34" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.34 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ISA 40:13">Is 40.13</ref> <char style="sc">lxx</char>; <ref loc="JOB 15:8">Job 15.8</ref>; <ref loc="JER 23:18">Jr 23.18</ref>; <ref loc="1CO 2:16">1 Cor 2.16</ref></char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">Τίς γὰρ ἔγνω νοῦν κυρίου;</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἢ τίς σύμβουλος αὐτοῦ ἐγένετο;</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="35" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.35 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="JOB 41:3">Job 41.3</ref>
      </char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">ἢ τίς προέδωκεν αὐτῷ,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ ἀνταποδοθήσεται αὐτῷ;</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="36" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">11.36 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἐξ … πάντα </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="1CO 8:6">1 Cor 8.6</ref>
      </char>
    </note>ὅτι ἐξ αὐτοῦ καὶ δι᾽ αὐτοῦ καὶ εἰς αὐτὸν τὰ πάντα· αὐτῷ ἡ δόξα εἰς τοὺς αἰῶνας, ἀμήν.</para>
  <chapter number="12" style="c" />
  <para style="s">The New Life in Christ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />Παρακαλῶ οὖν ὑμᾶς, ἀδελφοί, διὰ τῶν οἰκτιρμῶν τοῦ θεοῦ<note caller="a" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">C: AD M TR GNB NIV NRSV (REB) EU LB</char></note> παραστῆσαι τὰ σώματα ὑμῶν θυσίαν ζῶσαν ἁγίαν εὐάρεστον τῷ θεῷ, τὴν λογικὴν λατρείαν ὑμῶν· <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.1‑2 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">παραστῆσαι … εὐάρεστον </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 6:11">Ro 6.11</ref>, <ref loc="ROM 6:13">13</ref>; <ref loc="1PE 2:5">1 Pe 2.5</ref></char></note><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.2 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μεταμορφοῦσθε … νοός </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EPH 4:23">Eph 4.23</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">εἰς … τέλειον </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EPH 5:10">Eph 5.10</ref>, <ref loc="EPH 5:17">17</ref></char></note>καὶ μὴ συσχηματίζεσθε τῷ αἰῶνι τούτῳ, ἀλλὰ μεταμορφοῦσθε τῇ ἀνακαινώσει τοῦ νοὸς εἰς τὸ δοκιμάζειν ὑμᾶς τί τὸ θέλημα τοῦ θεοῦ,<note caller="b" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12.2 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">NO C: TR NRSV<char style="add">mg</char></char></note> τὸ ἀγαθὸν καὶ εὐάρεστον καὶ τέλειον.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">12.3 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἑκάστῳ … πίστεως </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="1CO 12:11">1 Cor 12.11</ref>; <ref loc="EPH 4:7">Eph 4.7</ref></char>
    </note>Λέγω γὰρ διὰ τῆς χάριτος τῆς δοθείσης μοι παντὶ τῷ ὄντι ἐν ὑμῖν μὴ ὑπερφρονεῖν παρ᾽ ὃ δεῖ φρονεῖν ἀλλὰ φρονεῖν εἰς τὸ σωφρονεῖν, ἑκάστῳ ὡς ὁ θεὸς ἐμέρισεν μέτρον πίστεως. <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1CO 12:12">1 Cor 12.12</ref></char></note>καθάπερ γὰρ ἐν ἑνὶ σώματι πολλὰ μέλη ἔχομεν, τὰ δὲ μέλη πάντα οὐ τὴν αὐτὴν ἔχει πρᾶξιν, <verse number="5" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.5 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1CO 12:27">1 Cor 12.27</ref>; <ref loc="EPH 4:25">Eph 4.25</ref></char></note>οὕτως οἱ πολλοὶ ἓν σῶμά ἐσμεν ἐν Χριστῷ, τὸ δὲ καθ᾽ εἷς ἀλλήλων μέλη. <verse number="6" style="v" />ἔχοντες δὲ χαρίσματα κατὰ τὴν χάριν τὴν δοθεῖσαν ἡμῖν διάφορα, εἴτε προφητείαν κατὰ τὴν ἀναλογίαν τῆς πίστεως, <verse number="7" style="v" />εἴτε διακονίαν ἐν τῇ διακονίᾳ, εἴτε ὁ διδάσκων ἐν τῇ διδασκαλίᾳ, <verse number="8" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.6‑8 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1CO 12:4-11">1 Cor 12.4‑11</ref>; <ref loc="1PE 4:10-11">1 Pe 4.10‑11</ref></char></note><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.8 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ μεταδιδοὺς ἐν ἁπλότητι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2CO 9:7">2 Cor 9.7</ref></char></note>εἴτε ὁ παρακαλῶν ἐν τῇ παρακλήσει· ὁ μεταδιδοὺς ἐν ἁπλότητι, ὁ προϊστάμενος ἐν σπουδῇ, ὁ ἐλεῶν ἐν ἱλαρότητι.</para>
  <para style="s">Rules of the Christian Life</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">12.9 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Ἡ ἀγάπη ἀνυπόκριτος </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="1TI 1:5">1 Tm 1.5</ref>; <ref loc="1PE 1:22">1 Pe 1.22</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἀποστυγοῦντες … ἀγαθῷ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="AMO 5:15">Am 5.15</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Ἡ ἀγάπη ἀνυπόκριτος. ἀποστυγοῦντες τὸ πονηρόν, κολλώμενοι τῷ ἀγαθῷ, <verse number="10" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.10 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῇ φιλαδελφίᾳ … φιλόστοργοι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2PE 1:7">2 Pe 1.7</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῇ τιμῇ … προηγούμενοι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PHP 2:3">Php 2.3</ref></char></note>τῇ φιλαδελφίᾳ εἰς ἀλλήλους φιλόστοργοι, τῇ τιμῇ ἀλλήλους προηγούμενοι, <verse number="11" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.11 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῷ πνεύματι ζέοντες </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 18:25">Ac 18.25</ref>; <ref loc="REV 3:15">Re 3.15</ref></char></note>τῇ σπουδῇ μὴ ὀκνηροί, τῷ πνεύματι ζέοντες, τῷ κυρίῳ<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12.11 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κυρίῳ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> ℵ A B D<char style="add">2</char> Ψ 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1852 1881 1962 2127 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, b, d<char style="add">2</char>, f, o, s, (t)</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, fay</char> arm eth geo slav Clement Origen<char style="add">lat1/2</char> Greek mss<char style="add">acc. to Origen<char style="add">lat</char></char> Basil Chrysostom; Greek mss<char style="add">acc. to Ambrosiaster <char style="it">and</char> Jerome</char> Jerome<char style="add">1/2</char> Pelagius Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καιρῷ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D<char style="add">*, 3</char> F G it<char style="add">d*, g</char> Origen<char style="add">lat1/2</char>; Latin mss<char style="add">acc. to Origen<char style="add">lat</char> <char style="it">and</char> Jerome</char> Cyprian Ambrosiaster Jerome<char style="add">1/2</char> ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῷ κυρίῳ δουλεύοντες </char><char style="ft" closed="false">1912</char></note> δουλεύοντες, <verse number="12" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.12 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῇ προσευχῇ προσκαρτεροῦντες </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1TH 5:17">1 Th 5.17</ref></char></note>τῇ ἐλπίδι χαίροντες, τῇ θλίψει ὑπομένοντες, τῇ προσευχῇ προσκαρτεροῦντες, <verse number="13" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.13 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τὴν φιλοξενίαν διώκοντες </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="HEB 13:2">He 13.2</ref></char></note>ταῖς χρείαις τῶν ἁγίων κοινωνοῦντες, τὴν φιλοξενίαν διώκοντες. <verse number="14" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 5:44">Mt 5.44</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 6:28">Lk 6.28</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 7:60">Ac 7.60</ref>; <ref loc="1CO 4:12">1 Cor 4.12</ref></char></note>εὐλογεῖτε τοὺς διώκοντας [ὑμᾶς]<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12.14 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">διώκοντας ὑμᾶς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A (D <char style="it">in another position</char>) Ψ 33<char style="add">vid</char> 81 104 256 263 365 424* 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1852 1881 1912 1962 2127 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">(b), d, s</char> vg<char style="add">cl</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, fay</char> arm eth geo slav Origen<char style="add">lat1/4</char> Basil Chrysostom; Ambrose Pelagius Augustine<char style="add">2/6</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">διώκοντας </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> B 6 424<char style="add">c</char> 1739 vg<char style="add">ww, st</char> Clement ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εὐλογεῖτε … ὑμᾶς </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">(homoioteleuton?)</char> F G it<char style="add">ar, f, g, o</char> syr<char style="add">pal</char> Marcion<char style="add">acc. to Tertullian<char style="add">vid</char></char> Origen<char style="add">lat3/4vid</char>; Cyprian<char style="add">vid</char> Ambrosiaster Jerome<char style="add">vid</char> Optatus<char style="add">vid</char> Augustine<char style="add">4/6vid</char> Speculum</char></note>, εὐλογεῖτε καὶ μὴ καταρᾶσθε. <verse number="15" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.15 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">κλαίειν μετὰ κλαιόντων </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 35:13">Ps 35.13</ref></char></note>χαίρειν μετὰ χαιρόντων, κλαίειν μετὰ κλαιόντων. <verse number="16" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.16 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τὸ αὐτὸ … φρονοῦντες </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 15:5">Ro 15.5</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ γίνεσθε … ἑαυτοῖς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PRO 3:7">Pr 3.7</ref>; <ref loc="ISA 5:21">Is 5.21</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 11:20">Ro 11.20</ref></char></note>τὸ αὐτὸ εἰς ἀλλήλους φρονοῦντες, μὴ τὰ ὑψηλὰ φρονοῦντες ἀλλὰ τοῖς ταπεινοῖς συναπαγόμενοι. μὴ γίνεσθε φρόνιμοι παρ᾽ ἑαυτοῖς. <verse number="17" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.17 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μηδενὶ … ἀποδιδόντες </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1TH 5:15">1 Th 5.15</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">προνοούμενοι … ἀνθρώπων </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PRO 3:4">Pr 3.4</ref> <char style="sc">lxx</char></char></note>μηδενὶ κακὸν ἀντὶ κακοῦ ἀποδιδόντες, προνοούμενοι καλὰ ἐνώπιον πάντων ἀνθρώπων· <verse number="18" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 9:50">Mk 9.50</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 12:14">He 12.14</ref></char></note>εἰ δυνατὸν τὸ ἐξ ὑμῶν, μετὰ πάντων ἀνθρώπων εἰρηνεύοντες· <verse number="19" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.19 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ ἑαυτοὺς ἐκδικοῦντες </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 19:18">Lv 19.18</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 5:39">Mt 5.39</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">δότε … ὀργῇ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 13:4">Ro 13.4</ref>; <ref loc="2TH 1:6-7">2 Th 1.6‑7</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἐμοὶ … ἀνταποδώσω </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 32:35">Dt 32.35</ref> (<ref loc="HEB 10:30">He 10.30</ref>)</char></note>μὴ ἑαυτοὺς ἐκδικοῦντες, ἀγαπητοί, ἀλλὰ δότε τόπον τῇ ὀργῇ, γέγραπται γάρ, <char style="qt">Ἐμοὶ ἐκδίκησις, ἐγὼ ἀνταποδώσω,</char> λέγει κύριος. <verse number="20" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">12.20 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐὰν … αὐτοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PRO 25:21-22">Pr 25.21‑22</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 5:44">Mt 5.44</ref></char></note>ἀλλ᾽ <char style="qt">ἐὰν πεινᾷ ὁ ἐχθρός σου, ψώμιζε αὐτόν· ἐὰν διψᾷ, πότιζε αὐτόν· τοῦτο γὰρ ποιῶν ἄνθρακας πυρὸς σωρεύσεις ἐπὶ τὴν κεφαλὴν αὐτοῦ.</char> <verse number="21" style="v" />μὴ νικῶ ὑπὸ τοῦ κακοῦ ἀλλὰ νίκα ἐν τῷ ἀγαθῷ τὸ κακόν.</para>
  <chapter number="13" style="c" />
  <para style="s">Obedience to Rulers</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">13.1 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Πᾶσα … ὑποτασσέσθω </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="TIT 3:1">Tt 3.1</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οὐ γὰρ … τεταγμέναι εἰσίν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="PRO 8:15">Pr 8.15</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 19:11">Jn 19.11</ref></char>
    </note>Πᾶσα ψυχὴ ἐξουσίαις ὑπερεχούσαις ὑποτασσέσθω<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">13.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πᾶσα ψυχὴ ἐξουσίαις ὑπερεχούσαις ὑποτασσέσθω </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B D<char style="add">2</char> Ψ 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1852 1881 1912 1962 2127 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 1356 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐξουσίας ἐχούσης</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">d<char style="add">2</char>, gue, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, (bo)</char> arm geo slav Origen Acacius Basil Didymus Chrysostom; Jerome Pelagius Augustine Speculum<char style="add">1/2</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πάσαις ἐξουσίαις ὑπερεχούσαις ὑποτάσσεσθε </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> D* F G it<char style="add">ar, b, d*, f, g, t</char> vg<char style="add">mss</char> (eth) Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Hippolytus; (Tertullian) Ambrosiaster Speculum<char style="add">1/2</char> Cassiodorus Sedulius-Scotus</char></note>. οὐ γὰρ ἔστιν ἐξουσία εἰ μὴ ὑπὸ θεοῦ, αἱ δὲ οὖσαι ὑπὸ θεοῦ τεταγμέναι εἰσίν. <verse number="2" style="v" />ὥστε ὁ ἀντιτασσόμενος τῇ ἐξουσίᾳ τῇ τοῦ θεοῦ διαταγῇ ἀνθέστηκεν, οἱ δὲ ἀνθεστηκότες ἑαυτοῖς κρίμα λήμψονται. <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13.3 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οἱ γὰρ … κακῷ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1PE 2:13-14">1 Pe 2.13‑14</ref>; <ref loc="1PE 3:13">3.13</ref></char></note>οἱ γὰρ ἄρχοντες οὐκ εἰσὶν φόβος τῷ ἀγαθῷ ἔργῳ ἀλλὰ τῷ κακῷ. θέλεις δὲ μὴ φοβεῖσθαι τὴν ἐξουσίαν· τὸ ἀγαθὸν ποίει, καὶ ἕξεις ἔπαινον ἐξ αὐτῆς· <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13.4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἔκδικος … πράσσοντι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 12:19">Ro 12.19</ref></char></note>θεοῦ γὰρ διάκονός ἐστιν σοὶ εἰς τὸ ἀγαθόν. ἐὰν δὲ τὸ κακὸν ποιῇς, φοβοῦ· οὐ γὰρ εἰκῇ τὴν μάχαιραν φορεῖ· θεοῦ γὰρ διάκονός ἐστιν ἔκδικος εἰς ὀργὴν τῷ τὸ κακὸν πράσσοντι. <verse number="5" style="v" />διὸ ἀνάγκη ὑποτάσσεσθαι, οὐ μόνον διὰ τὴν ὀργὴν ἀλλὰ καὶ διὰ τὴν συνείδησιν. <verse number="6" style="v" />διὰ τοῦτο γὰρ καὶ φόρους τελεῖτε· λειτουργοὶ γὰρ θεοῦ εἰσιν εἰς αὐτὸ τοῦτο προσκαρτεροῦντες. <verse number="7" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13.7 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἀπόδοτε … φόρον </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 22:21">Mt 22.21</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 12:17">Mk 12.17</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:25">Lk 20.25</ref></char></note>ἀπόδοτε πᾶσιν τὰς ὀφειλάς, τῷ τὸν φόρον τὸν φόρον, τῷ τὸ τέλος τὸ τέλος, τῷ τὸν φόβον τὸν φόβον, τῷ τὴν τιμὴν τὴν τιμήν.</para>
  <para style="s">Brotherly Love</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">13.8 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ γὰρ … πεπλήρωκεν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="GAL 5:14">Ga 5.14</ref>; <ref loc="1TI 1:5">1 Tm 1.5</ref></char>
    </note>Μηδενὶ μηδὲν ὀφείλετε εἰ μὴ τὸ ἀλλήλους ἀγαπᾶν· ὁ γὰρ ἀγαπῶν τὸν ἕτερον νόμον πεπλήρωκεν. <verse number="9" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13.9 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Οὐ μοιχεύσεις … ἐπιθυμήσεις </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 20:13-15">Ex 20.13‑15</ref>, <ref loc="EXO 20:17">17</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 5:17-19">Dt 5.17‑19</ref>, <ref loc="DEU 5:21">21</ref> (<ref loc="MAT 19:18">Mt 19.18</ref>) </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἀγαπήσεις … σεαυτόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LEV 19:18">Lv 19.18</ref> (<ref loc="MAT 5:43">Mt 5.43</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 19:19">19.19</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 22:39">22.39</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 12:31">Mk 12.31</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 10:27">Lk 10.27</ref>; <ref loc="GAL 5:14">Ga 5.14</ref>; <ref loc="JAS 2:8">Jas 2.8</ref>)</char></note>τὸ γὰρ <char style="qt">Οὐ μοιχεύσεις, Οὐ φονεύσεις, Οὐ κλέψεις, Οὐκ ἐπιθυμήσεις</char><note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">13.9 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐ κλέψεις, οὐκ ἐπιθυμήσεις </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> A B D F G Ψ 6 33 1175 1241 1739 1881 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char><char style="add">pt</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">d, f, g, o</char> vg<char style="add">ww, st</char> syr<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">sa</char> geo Clement<char style="add">1/2</char> Basil; Ambrosiaster Ambrose Jerome<char style="add">1/2</char> Pelagius Augustine<char style="add">8/15</char> (Hesychius<char style="add">lat</char> Augustine<char style="add">6/15</char> <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐ κλέψεις</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐ κλέψεις </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Marcion<char style="add">acc. to Adamantius</char> Clement<char style="add">1/2</char> Orige