  <para style="s">The Approach of the Day of Christ</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">13.11 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">εἰδότες … ἐγερθῆναι </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="EPH 5:14">Eph 5.14</ref>; <ref loc="1TH 5:6-7">1 Th 5.6‑7</ref></char>
    </note>Καὶ τοῦτο εἰδότες τὸν καιρόν, ὅτι ὥρα ἤδη ὑμᾶς<note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">13.11 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὑμᾶς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ* A B C P 81 365 1319 1852 1881 (1962 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὑμᾶς ἤδη</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 2127 it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, g, o</char> vg cop<char style="add">bo</char> slav Clement Pachomius<char style="add">lat</char> Cyril; Ambrosiaster Jerome Pelagius Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμᾶς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46vid</char> ℵ<char style="add">2</char> D (F G L 1175 1912 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμᾶς ἤδη</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) Ψ 0150 6 33 104 256 263 424 436 459 1241 1506 1573 1739 1912 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> syr<char style="add">p, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa</char> arm geo Chrysostom DHH ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> eth Origen<char style="add">lat</char></char></note> ἐξ ὕπνου ἐγερθῆναι, νῦν γὰρ ἐγγύτερον ἡμῶν ἡ σωτηρία ἢ ὅτε ἐπιστεύσαμεν. <verse number="12" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13.12 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἡ νὺξ … ἤγγικεν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1JN 2:8">1 Jn 2.8</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἀποθώμεθα … σκότους </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EPH 5:11">Eph 5.11</ref></char></note>ἡ νὺξ προέκοψεν, ἡ δὲ ἡμέρα ἤγγικεν. ἀποθώμεθα<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">13.12 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀποθώμεθα </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C D<char style="add">2</char> Ψ 048 0150 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1852 (1881 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀποθέμενοι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 1912 1962 2127 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> slav Clement Pachomius<char style="add">lat</char> (Gregory-Nyssa) Didymus Chrysostom Cyril Proclus Theodoret; Quodvultdeus ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀποβαλώμεθα </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> D<char style="add">*, 3</char> F G eth REB TOB?</char></note> οὖν τὰ ἔργα τοῦ σκότους, ἐνδυσώμεθα [δὲ] τὰ ὅπλα τοῦ φωτός. <verse number="13" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13.13 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὡς … μέθαις </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 21:34">Lk 21.34</ref>; <ref loc="EPH 5:18">Eph 5.18</ref></char></note>ὡς ἐν ἡμέρᾳ εὐσχημόνως περιπατήσωμεν, μὴ κώμοις καὶ μέθαις, μὴ κοίταις καὶ ἀσελγείαις, μὴ ἔριδι καὶ ζήλῳ, <verse number="14" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">13.14 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐνδύσασθε … Χριστόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GAL 3:27">Ga 3.27</ref></char></note>ἀλλ᾽ ἐνδύσασθε τὸν κύριον Ἰησοῦν Χριστὸν καὶ τῆς σαρκὸς πρόνοιαν μὴ ποιεῖσθε εἰς ἐπιθυμίας.</para>
  <chapter number="14" style="c" />
  <para style="s">Do Not Judge Your Brother</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">14.1 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Τὸν δὲ … προσλαμβάνεσθε </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ROM 15:7">Ro 15.7</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Τὸν δὲ ἀσθενοῦντα τῇ πίστει προσλαμβάνεσθε, μὴ εἰς διακρίσεις διαλογισμῶν. <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">14.2 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 1:29">Gn 1.29</ref>; <ref loc="GEN 9:3">9.3</ref></char></note>ὃς μὲν πιστεύει φαγεῖν πάντα, ὁ δὲ ἀσθενῶν λάχανα ἐσθίει. <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">14.3 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="COL 2:16">Col 2.16</ref></char></note>ὁ ἐσθίων τὸν μὴ ἐσθίοντα μὴ ἐξουθενείτω, ὁ δὲ μὴ ἐσθίων τὸν ἐσθίοντα μὴ κρινέτω, ὁ θεὸς γὰρ αὐτὸν προσελάβετο. <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">14.4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">σὺ … κρίνων </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 7:1">Mt 7.1</ref>; <ref loc="JAS 4:11-12">Jas 4.11‑12</ref></char></note>σὺ τίς εἶ ὁ κρίνων ἀλλότριον οἰκέτην; τῷ ἰδίῳ κυρίῳ στήκει ἢ πίπτει· σταθήσεται δέ, δυνατεῖ γὰρ ὁ κύριος<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">14.4 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κύριος </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">46</char> ℵ A B C P Ψ 1852 (syr<char style="add">p</char>) cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm geo<char style="add">1</char> slav<char style="add">ms</char> Severian; Optatus Augustine<char style="add">1/6</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">θεός </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(<char style="it">see</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 14:3">14.3</ref>)</char> D F G 048 0150 6 33 81 104 256 263 365 424 436 459 1175 1241 1319 1506 1573 1739 1881 1912 1962 2127 2200 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, g, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> geo<char style="add">2</char> slav<char style="add">ms</char> Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Basil Chrysostom; Cyprian Ps-Cyprian Amb