se">14.23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="TIT 1:15">Tt 1.15</ref></char></note>ὁ δὲ διακρινόμενος ἐὰν φάγῃ κατακέκριται, ὅτι οὐκ ἐκ πίστεως· πᾶν δὲ ὃ οὐκ ἐκ πίστεως ἁμαρτία ἐστίν<note caller="9" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">14.23 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐστίν. </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(<char style="it">see</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 15:33">15.33</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 16:25">16.25</ref>)</char> ℵ B C D 048 81 256 263 365 436 1319 1573 1739 1852 1962 2127 2200 it<char style="add">ar, b, d, f, r, o</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> eth mss<char style="add">acc. to Origen<char style="add">lat</char></char>; Ambrosiaster Pelagius Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐστίν. </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">plus</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 16:25-27">16.25‑27</ref></char> <char style="it">here only</char> Ψ 0209<char style="add">vid</char> 6 424 1175 1241 1881 1912 <char style="it">Byz</char> [L] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">gue<char style="add">vid</char>, (mon<char style="add">vid</char>)</char> vg<char style="add">mss</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> geo<char style="add">2</char> slav mss<char style="add">acc. to Origen<char style="add">lat</char></char> Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐστίν </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">plus</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 16:25-27">16.25‑27</ref></char> <char style="it">both here and at</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 16:23">16.23</ref></char> A P 0150 33 104 459 arm geo<char style="add">1</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐστίν. </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">plus</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 16:25-27">16.25‑27</ref></char> <char style="it">at</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ROM 15:33">15.33</ref></char>